# PoC Project Layout

This repository is a proof-of-concept hub published with GitHub Pages at `poc.stanho.dev`.

Use a single static Vite + React + TypeScript app that hosts many small PoCs.

Recommended structure:

```text
public/
  CNAME
  assets/
src/
  components/
    Layout.tsx
    PocCard.tsx
  pages/
    Home.tsx
    PocPage.tsx
  pocs/
    registry.ts
    example-poc/
      Demo.tsx
      README.md
      assets/
  styles/
    globals.css
```

Guidelines:

- Keep each PoC self-contained in `src/pocs/<poc-name>/`.
- Register visible PoCs in `src/pocs/registry.ts`.
- Prefer URLs like `/pocs/<poc-name>`.
- Keep shared UI in `src/components/`.
- Keep page-level routing/layout in `src/pages/`.
- Use `public/CNAME` with `poc.stanho.dev` for the custom GitHub Pages domain.
- Avoid turning each PoC into a separate app unless there is a clear reason.
